  "notes": "Classical/Standard Tibetan (Lhasa variety). The Tibetan script is an abugida; consonant letters carry an inherent /a/ vowel unless a vowel diacritic is present. Many prefix/suffix letters are silent in spoken Lhasa Tibetan. Voiced vs. voiceless distinction in classical spelling corresponds to tonal distinction in spoken Lhasa Tibetan. This spec represents spelling-to-classical-pronunciation mapping; Lhasa colloquial differs significantly.",
